# Tomifoci 2026 — Project Governor

This governor is the operating prompt for the full rewrite of VB Tippjáték 2026.
It governs how AI threads work in this repo from 2026-06-28 onwards.

---

## 0. Current State (as of 2026-06-30 — migration complete)

The live game now runs on **Next.js + Neon (Postgres) + Vercel**, in the standalone
**`tomifoci.xyz`** repo (extracted from `apps/rewrite/`). **Neon is the only live
database.** The original **vanilla JS + Convex + Cloudflare** stack in this repo is the
**retired legacy "classic"** — kept for reference and as a fallback *source* only. The
phase plan below is preserved as the historical record of how the migration was run; it
is no longer an active to-do list.

> Do **not** treat this project as "a Convex app." Convex is retired and read-only.

Key facts:
- The live product is the `tomifoci.xyz` repo on Vercel; its own `CLAUDE.md` /
  `.claude/memory.md` are authoritative for the running stack.
- A classic-UI **fallback** at a `/classic/` path (rewired to read the Neon `/api/state`)
  is planned but not yet built — see the fallback build plan in the `tomifoci.xyz` repo.
- `design_handoff_vbtippjatek_redesign/` has the final designs: Concept B player app,
  Brackets, Admin.
- `SPEC_DIGEST.md` has all testable game-rule assertions (SCORE-01…INV-15) — still the
  canonical rules reference.

---

## 1. Hard Rules

1. **Classic game stays live.** Never touch `index 2.html`, `js/*.js`, `css/*.css`, `convex/*`
   during the rewrite. The only exception is running the export/sync script.
2. **Database structure is fixed.** Do not add or remove Neon columns unless a new
   feature explicitly requires it and is approved. The Drizzle schema in
   `apps/rewrite/db/schema.ts` is the contract.
3. **Server-Driven UI.** Every player-facing and admin-facing screen must be backed by
   a SurfaceDefinition from `@rhnd/server-driven-ui-*`. The server owns the component tree;
   the client renders what the server says.
4. **Backend-first.** Every frontend function must have a corresponding API route + DB query
   before the component is built. No orphan UI.
5. **Convex is source of truth until Neon sync is verified.** After sync is verified and
   diffed, Convex is archived (read-only). Never write to Convex from the rewrite app.
6. **Game mechanics are extracted, not reimplemented.** Copy `calcPts`, `getActiveFav`,
   Wizard scoring, and Swiss compute from `convex/scoring.ts` / `convex/wizard.ts` /
   `convex/swiss.ts` into `packages/game-engine/`. Do not invent new rules.
7. **Verify before claim.** Before stating a file, function, route, or package exists:
   check it. Do not invent paths or API names.
8. **Journal every session.** Append an entry to `JOURNAL.md` at the end of each session.
   Follow the RHND journal format (frontmatter + dated sections).

---

## 2. Build Loop (per session)

1. Read this governor.
2. Read `tasks/todo.md` — find the first unchecked item.
3. Read only the files directly referenced by that task.
4. Implement the task.
5. Run the task's verification commands.
6. Check off the item in `tasks/todo.md`.
7. Append to `JOURNAL.md`.
8. Stop — do not continue to the next phase unless the user asks.

---

## 3. Stack Decisions

| Layer | Choice | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Monorepo | Turborepo (already configured) | `turbo.json` at root |
| Frontend | Next.js 16 (App Router) | `apps/rewrite/` |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 + `@rhnd/tailwind-ui` | BROADCAST token mapping |
| UI pattern | `@rhnd/server-driven-ui-next` | SurfaceDefinition per screen |
| Database | Neon (Postgres) via `@neondatabase/serverless` | Drizzle ORM |
| Auth | PIN hash (bcrypt/argon2id) stored in Neon `imported_rows` | No JWT initially |
| Cron | Vercel cron (`vercel.json` `crons`) | Replace Convex crons |
| Push | `web-push` library, subscriptions in Neon | Same VAPID keys |
| Classic backup | `/classic/` path in Next.js, proxies or static | Until smoke tests pass |

---

## 4. Model Assignment

> Rule: one thread per model/phase (prompt cache is per-model; cross-model threads re-send
> growing context and destroy cache efficiency). Set the model before the first message.

| Phase | Tag | Model |
|---|---|---|
| P0 Housekeeping | `P0.Sonnet` | Sonnet |
| P1 Neon Sync | `P1.Sonnet` | Sonnet |
| P2 Backend routes | `P2.Sonnet` / `P2-SEC.Opus` | Sonnet (Opus for auth routes) |
| P3 Game engine | `P3.Sonnet` | Sonnet |
| P4 Surface layer | `P4.Sonnet` / `P4-SEC.Opus` | Sonnet (Opus for HMAC/policy) |
| P5 Frontend | `P5.Sonnet` | Sonnet |
| P6 Integrations | `P6.Sonnet` | Sonnet |
| P7 Mechanics comparison | `P7.Haiku` | **Haiku** — 60 structured assertions, pass/fail classification |
| P8 Cutover | `P8.Sonnet` | Sonnet |
| Each checkpoint security gate | `CHK.Opus` | **Opus** — security review |

---

## 5. Phase Plan

Phases are sequential. Each phase ends with a verification gate before the next starts.

### Phase 0 — Housekeeping
Outcome: docs in order, packages installed, old plans archived.

### Phase 1 — Neon Sync
Outcome: all Convex tables mirrored in Neon; state diff passes; Convex archived.

### Phase 2 — Backend Data Layer
Outcome: for every entity, a typed read route (GET) and write route (POST/PUT/DELETE)
backed by Neon. All routes map 1:1 to the functional inventory (BE-001…BE-034).

### Phase 3 — Game Engine Package
Outcome: `packages/game-engine/` contains pure TS functions: `calcPts`, `getActiveFav`,
`computeAllScores`, `computeWizardScores`, `computeSwiss`. Tested against SPEC_DIGEST.

### Phase 4 — Server-Driven UI Surface Layer
Outcome: every screen has a SurfaceDefinition in `apps/rewrite/lib/surfaces/`.
The surface registry covers: landing, login, meccsek, tabella, profil, brackets, admin/*.

### Phase 5 — Frontend
Outcome: all screens from Concept B + Brackets + Admin built in Next.js using
Tailwind UI components. Design matches `design_handoff_vbtippjatek_redesign/README.md` exactly.

### Phase 6 — Integrations
Outcome: Vercel cron replaces Convex crons for LiveScore polling, auto-recompute,
Swiss auto-publish. Web push works with existing subscriptions.

### Phase 7 — Mechanics Comparison & Smoke Tests
Outcome: every SPEC_DIGEST assertion (SCORE-01…SWISS-18, INV-01…INV-15) checked
against the new engine. Differences documented in `tasks/mechanics-diff.md`.

### Phase 8 — Cutover
Outcome: DNS switched to Vercel. Classic game frozen. Old Cloudflare/Convex on standby.

---

## 5. Invariants (must hold throughout)

All invariants from `SPEC_DIGEST.md` (INV-01…INV-15) apply to the new stack unchanged:
- INV-01: predictions + results are immutable truth; everything else derived.
- INV-02: player identity = name string; cascades on rename/delete.
- INV-03: recompute pipeline runs in order after every truth mutation.
- INV-09: secrets never in public state response.
- INV-10: kickoff lock enforced server-side.

---

## 6. Security Baseline

- Admin PIN: bcrypt hash in Neon `imported_rows`, never in session/local storage.
- Player PIN: same. Server-side verification only.
- Rate limiting on auth routes: escalating lockout (mirror `authAttempts` table).
- Server actions: every mutating surface action requires re-verification of PIN or
  admin session token.
- SurfaceDefinition signatures: use HMAC-SHA256 from `@rhnd/server-driven-ui-core`.

---

## 7. Journaling Protocol

Append to `JOURNAL.md` after each working session:

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD — Phase N Session N: <one-line title>

### Completed
- [task-id] Brief description — file:line

### Not Completed (and why)
- …

### Verification
- `pnpm typecheck` — PASS / FAIL
- `pnpm test` — PASS / FAIL / n tests

### Next Action
[First task for the next session, exact todo id]
```
